# Environment Configuration

This file contains example environment variables for the Real-time Titling Service.

## Server Configuration
PORT=3001
NODE_ENV=development

## STT Service Configuration
# Options: mock, google, openai, local
STT_SERVICE=mock

## Google Cloud Speech-to-Text Configuration
# Required if STT_SERVICE=google
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=path/to/service-account-key.json
GOOGLE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id

## OpenAI API Configuration
# Required if STT_SERVICE=openai
OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-api-key

## Local AI Service Configuration
# Required if STT_SERVICE=local
LOCAL_AI_URL=http://localhost:8080/v1/audio/transcriptions

## Translation Configuration
ENABLE_TRANSLATION=true
TARGET_LANGUAGE=en
SOURCE_LANGUAGE=sr

## WebSocket Configuration
WS_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL=30000
WS_MAX_CONNECTIONS=100

## Usage Instructions

1. Copy this file to `.env` in the project root
2. Update the values according to your setup
3. For production, ensure all sensitive values are properly secured

## Service-Specific Setup

### Mock Service (Default)
- No additional configuration required
- Perfect for development and testing

### Google Cloud Speech-to-Text
1. Create a Google Cloud project
2. Enable Speech-to-Text API
3. Create a service account and download the JSON key
4. Set GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS to the key file path
5. Set GOOGLE_PROJECT_ID to your project ID

### OpenAI Whisper
1. Get an API key from OpenAI
2. Set OPENAI_API_KEY to your key
3. Ensure you have sufficient credits

### Local AI Service
1. Set up LocalAI or similar service
2. Ensure it's running on the specified URL
3. Verify the API endpoints match OpenAI's format